{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_277d15d84ffeekUl332OtSRYrW","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d882eb72a001AOKVCeSuHkAiu0","parts":[{"id":"prt_d882ebf22001JvYIzIrQcQJkR7","messageID":"msg_d882eb72a001AOKVCeSuHkAiu0","sessionID":"ses_277d15d84ffeekUl332OtSRYrW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5a67bf3a472a4386af731eff","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: [![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/cellrank.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/cellrank)\n2: [![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/cellrank)](https://pepy.tech/project/cellrank)\n3: [![CI](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/theislab/cellrank/test.yaml?branch=main)](https://github.com/theislab/cellrank/actions)\n4: [![Docs](https://img.shields.io/readthedocs/cellrank)](https://cellrank.readthedocs.io/)\n5: [![Codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/theislab/cellrank/branch/main/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/theislab/cellrank)\n6: [![Discourse](https://img.shields.io/discourse/posts?color=yellow&logo=discourse&server=https%3A%2F%2Fdiscourse.scverse.org)](https://discourse.scverse.org/c/ecosystem/cellrank/)\n7: [![Python Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/cellrank)](https://pypi.org/project/cellrank)\n8: \n9: # CellRank 2: Unified fate mapping in multiview single-cell data\n10: \n11: <!-- image-start -->\n12: <picture>\n13:   <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/scverse/cellrank/main/docs/_static/img/dark_mode_overview.png\">\n14:   <img alt=\"CellRank overview\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/scverse/cellrank/main/docs/_static/img/light_mode_overview.png\" width=\"600px\" align=\"center\">\n15: </picture>\n16: <!-- image-end -->\n17: \n18: **CellRank** is a modular framework to study cellular dynamics based on Markov state modeling of\n19: multi-view single-cell data. See our [documentation], and the [CellRank 1] and [CellRank 2] manuscripts to learn more.\n20: Read a summary of the CellRank papers [here](https://cellrank.readthedocs.io/en/latest/about/cite.html#cellrank-papers).\n21: \n22: ⚠️ **Please refer to [our citation guide](https://cellrank.readthedocs.io/en/latest/about/cite.html) to cite our software correctly.**\n23: \n24: CellRank scales to large cell numbers, is fully compatible with the [scverse] ecosystem, and is easy to use.\n25: In the backend, it is powered by [pyGPCCA] ([Reuter et al. (2018)]). Feel\n26: free to open an [issue] if you encounter a bug, need our help, or just want to make a comment/suggestion.\n27: \n28: ## CellRank's key applications\n29: \n30: - Estimate differentiation direction based on a varied number of biological priors, including RNA velocity\n31:   ([La Manno et al. (2018)], [Bergen et al. (2020)]), any pseudotime or developmental potential,\n32:   experimental time points, metabolic labels, and more.\n33: - Compute initial, terminal and intermediate macrostates.\n34: - Infer fate probabilities and driver genes.\n35: - Visualize and cluster gene expression trends.\n36: - ... and much more, check out our [documentation].\n37: \n38: ## Installation\n39: \n40: ```bash\n41: pip install cellrank\n42: ```\n43: \n44: See the [installation guide](https://cellrank.readthedocs.io/en/latest/installation.html) for more options.\n45: \n46: ## Related packages\n47: \n48: If you like CellRank, check out these packages from the same authors.\n49: Almost all are part of the [scverse ecosystem].\n50: \n51: | Package | Description | Reference |\n52: |---------|-------------|-----------|\n53: | [moscot] | Optimal transport for temporal, spatial, and spatio-temporal single-cell mapping | [Klein et al. (2025)] |\n54: | [moslin] | Trajectory inference with lineage barcodes via optimal transport (part of moscot) | [Lange et al. (2024)] |\n55: | [VeloVI] | RNA velocity with variational inference and uncertainty quantification (part of scvi-tools) | [Gayoso et al. (2024)] |\n56: | [RegVelo] | Jointly learning gene regulation and RNA velocity | [Wang et al. (2024)] |\n57: | [CellMapper] | kNN-based label, embedding, and molecular layer transfer between datasets | — |\n58: | [CellAnnotator] | LLM-based cell type annotation with support for major LLM providers | — |\n59: \n60: [moscot]: https://moscot.readthedocs.io/\n61: [moslin]: https://moscot.readthedocs.io/en/latest/notebooks/tutorials/100_lineage.html\n62: [VeloVI]: https://docs.scvi-tools.org/en/1.3.3/tutorials/notebooks/scrna/velovi.html\n63: [RegVelo]: https://regvelo.readthedocs.io/\n64: [CellMapper]: https://cellmapper.readthedocs.io/\n65: [CellAnnotator]: https://cell-annotator.readthedocs.io/\n66: [scverse ecosystem]: https://scverse.org/packages/#ecosystem\n67: [Klein et al. (2025)]: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-024-08453-2\n68: [Lange et al. (2024)]: https://doi.org/10.1186/s13059-024-03422-4\n69: [Gayoso et al. (2024)]: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-023-01994-w\n70: [Wang et al. (2024)]: https://doi.org/10.1101/2024.12.11.627935\n71: \n72: [La Manno et al. (2018)]: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-018-0414-6\n73: [Bergen et al. (2020)]: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41587-020-0591-3\n74: [Reuter et al. (2018)]: https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.jctc.8b00079\n75: [scverse]: https://scverse.org/\n76: [pyGPCCA]: https://github.com/msmdev/pyGPCCA\n77: [CellRank 1]: https://www.nature.com/articles/s41592-021-01346-6\n78: [CellRank 2]: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-024-02303-9\n79: [documentation]: https://cellrank.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\n80: [issue]: https://github.com/theislab/cellrank/issues/new/choose\n\n(End of file - total 80 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/cellrank.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/cellrank)\n[![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/cellrank)](https://pepy.tech/project/cellrank)\n[![CI](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/theislab/cellrank/test.yaml?branch=main)](https://github.com/theislab/cellrank/actions)\n[![Docs](https://img.shields.io/readthedocs/cellrank)](https://cellrank.readthedocs.io/)\n[![Codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/theislab/cellrank/branch/main/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/theislab/cellrank)\n[![Discourse](https://img.shields.io/discourse/posts?color=yellow&logo=discourse&server=https%3A%2F%2Fdiscourse.scverse.org)](https://discourse.scverse.org/c/ecosystem/cellrank/)\n[![Python Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/cellrank)](https://pypi.org/project/cellrank)\n\n# CellRank 2: Unified fate mapping in multiview single-cell data\n\n<!-- image-start -->\n<picture>\n  <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/scverse/cellrank/main/docs/_static/img/dark_mode_overview.png\">\n  <img alt=\"CellRank overview\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/scverse/cellrank/main/docs/_static/img/light_mode_overview.png\" width=\"600px\" align=\"center\">\n</picture>\n<!-- image-end -->\n\n**CellRank** is a modular framework to study cellular dynamics based on Markov state modeling of\nmulti-view single-cell data. See our [documentation], and the [CellRank 1] and [CellRank 2] manuscripts to learn more.\nRead a summary of the CellRank papers [here](https://cellrank.readthedocs.io/en/latest/about/cite.html#cellrank-papers).","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1776106258641,"end":1776106258652}}}]}
